<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <!--
    Menu-bar-only ("agent") launch state is owned SOLELY by the setup-time
    `set_activation_policy(Accessory)` in main.rs (mt#2219), which tao applies
    at applicationDidFinishLaunching — before any window can appear, so there
    is no Dock-icon flash at launch. The former declarative `LSUIElement`
    flag (mt#2202) was REMOVED in mt#2675: with it present, the runtime
    Accessory→Regular transform (`set_dock_presence`) never takes OS-level
    effect — the app stays out of Cmd-Tab and the Dock even after
    NSApp.setActivationPolicy(Regular) — so dynamic Dock presence requires
    the plist key to be absent (matches the community reference pattern,
    tauri-apps/tauri discussion #10774). Tauri v2's macOS bundler still
    merges this file into the generated Info.plist.
  -->
</dict>
</plist>
